cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper primarily focuses on evaluating the impact of mobility on wireless routing protocols in multi-hop wireless networks. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses performance parameters such as throughput and end-to-end delay, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may touch upon security concerns related to wireless routing protocols in passing. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper evaluates and compares the performance of different routing protocols, which involves analyzing their underlying algorithms and data structures. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may touch upon control theory concepts related to optimizing the performance of routing protocols.
